From: Surface Pro 11 bring-up <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] arm64: dts: qcom: x1-denali: test 2.4 MHz DMIC clock

The Surface Pro 11 internal microphones capture speech but retain persistent
broadband static at the current 4.8 MHz DMIC clock. Qualcomm's X1E CRD uses a
2.4 MHz DMIC clock, which is also supported by the VA macro driver.

Set the Denali DMIC sample clock to 2.4 MHz for a controlled test build. This
is an experiment, not a claim that 2.4 MHz is the final board setting.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/x1-microsoft-denali.dtsi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/x1-microsoft-denali.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/x1-microsoft-denali.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/x1-microsoft-denali.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/x1-microsoft-denali.dtsi
@@ -863,7 +863,7 @@ &lpass_vamacro {
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
 
 	vdd-micb-supply = <&vreg_l1b_1p8>;
-	qcom,dmic-sample-rate = <4800000>;
+	qcom,dmic-sample-rate = <2400000>;
 };
 
 &mdss {
-- 
2.50.1

